  "body": "[Solidity features](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Solidity-Features) wiki page contained the following section.  The documentation in this repository does not explain this feature yet.  This issue keeps track of adding such explanations to the this repository.\r\n\r\n\r\n> Inline members initialization\r\n> \r\n> This point seems to be missing from the official documentation.\r\n> \r\n> PT Inline members can be initialized at declaration time.\r\n> \r\n> contract test {\r\n>   function test(){\r\n>     m_b = 6;\r\n>   }\r\n>   uint m_a = 5;\r\n>   uint m_b;\r\n> }",
